    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "about",
      "title": "The Official Mascot\nYes her name is HCm3ErpbQAAMQ6I\nand I don't know how to pronounce it either.",
      "uuid": "6331d87abd4c47e2afc3779918ddfec7",
      "x": 2776.83745346258,
      "y": -688.620266126059,
      "width": 473.55158021299803,
      "height": 100.43053074549198,
      "z_value": 10.0,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": false,
      "label": "The Official Mascot\nYes her name is HCm3ErpbQAAMQ6I\nand I don't know how to pronounce it either.",
      "depth_front": true,
      "node_tint": "#1e1e1e"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Omnious",
      "uuid": "4d1296f6a14f41279b9f86a13d570384",
      "x": 994.8765083303949,
      "y": 4597.938266095083,
      "width": 752.6372551973357,
      "height": 308.20188757884955,
      "z_value": 10.0,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "\nHere's the full analysis \u2014 **top 10 most repeated patterns** across the codebase, ranked by frequency and extraction value:\n\n| **2** | **Paint data grid** (header \u2192 divider \u2192 label/value rows \u2192 footer) | 3 | `paint_data_grid(painter, rect, header, rows, fonts, colors)` |\n| **3** | **QTimer creation** (new \u2192 interval \u2192 connect \u2192 start) | ~14 | `create_timer(interval, callback, single_shot=False)` |\n| **4** | **Font with max(1, size) clamp** | 20+ | `make_font(family=None, size=None, bold=False)` |\n| **5** | **QPen / QBrush from theme color** | 30+ | `make_pen(color, width=1, style=SolidLine)` / `make_brush(color)` |\n| **6** | **Closest port search** (identical loop in input + output variants) | 4 | `closest_port(ports, scene_pos)` |\n| **8** | **Inset rect from padding/offsets** | 20+ | `inset_rect(base, top, bottom, left, right)` |\n| **9** | **QPropertyAnimation boilerplate** | 12+ | `create_animation(target, prop, start, end, duration, easing)` |\n\nKey observations:\n- Patterns 4 and 5 are the lowest-hanging fruit \u2014 one-liners that eliminate `max(1, ...)` and `QPen(QColor(...))` noise everywhere.\n- Pattern 2 (data grid painting) is higher complexity but would clean up the three monitor nodes significantly.\n"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "about",
      "title": "Note",
      "uuid": "48cd97b63f544e84ac92a958e81fb254",
      "x": 4121.182621134666,
      "y": 3337.1139946135954,
      "width": 131.87358272618235,
      "height": 36.26781751877974,
