    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "claude_response",
      "title": "Response",
      "uuid": "20b7f6c4bc964eccac6955d5b5162c6d",
      "x": 17641.025402546926,
      "y": 2819.867859609696,
      "width": 420.0,
      "height": 204.0,
      "z_value": -9.702000000000165,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "label": "Now it's vertically centred within the button zone strip \u2014 same row height as the tint/depth/close buttons, tucked into the right corner.",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "claude_response",
      "title": "Response",
      "uuid": "a2c7bfb358aa4e6ea7d981476b2b5309",
      "x": 17169.7099772332,
      "y": 6097.677546164887,
      "width": 394.88215487172465,
      "height": 144.2110359632511,
      "z_value": -9.83900000000009,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "label": "The NodeBehaviour pulse was always the heartbeat. The self-healing pan just gave it an immune system.",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "claude_response",
      "title": "Response",
      "uuid": "67c2e6905c9c434194fe1bc601e674dd",
      "x": 23330.639745343367,
      "y": 3115.3269041179774,
      "width": 420.0,
      "height": 428.0,
      "z_value": -10.0,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "label": "The pattern is clear now \u2014 every time Qt does something that disturbs the view/scene widget lifecycle (hide/show of the central widget, geometry resize during animation) there's a window where the scene's mouse state goes stale. The curtains restore is the third distinct trigger, so the right fix is a single shared cleanup that runs at the end of every curtains animation rather than patching each scenario individually.",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": "#9a4a4a"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "image",
      "title": "Image",
      "uuid": "df7263ed7ccc4cf995fa21fd15d84242",
      "x": 15418.583014340988,
      "y": 6744.938684806382,
      "width": 739.3828146247725,
      "height": 478.3538592102564,
      "z_value": -9.83800000000009,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": false,
      "image_b64": "",
      "cache_key": "297203e88a623ec2c5b8229b10e524396fb2c9f4cabd922943cace4002b7f688.png",
      "caption": "06 - Who would have such power",
      "source_path": "C:\\Users\\thisg\\Desktop\\The Dawn of a new Era of Mankind\\Yay\\06 - Who would have such power.png",
      "source_size": 683967,
      "source_mtime": 1770270249.0534933,
      "show_border": true,
      "depth_front": false
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "about",
      "title": "Note",
      "uuid": "c28b7f0e614f4e34a32af3ac85847149",
      "x": 17035.883813636694,
      "y": 3740.306772462606,
      "width": 88.0,
      "height": 52.0,
      "z_value": -10.0,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": false,
      "label": "Soft",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": "#b05f5f"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "claude_response",
      "title": "Response",
      "uuid": "cc0503425b844302898ed79464edfa88",
      "x": 19848.956028453562,
      "y": 2427.282556981877,
      "width": 420.0,
      "height": 428.0,
      "z_value": -10.0,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "label": "Found it. In `BaseNode.__init__`, `NodeBehaviour` is created at line 120, then `setBrush(Theme.nodeBg)` at line 133. `AboutNode` then overrides with `setBrush(self._bg_color())`. That part is fine. The bug is: when the shuffle button is clicked while hovering, `bg_anim` is still running with its old end value \u2014 it fires `_on_bg_changed` after `_apply_depth` sets the new brush, overwriting it. We need to stop the animation before resetting:",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": "#9a4a4a"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "claude_response",
      "title": "Response",
      "uuid": "bf6105ca7bfd4f6b9603b37ea2d3bbb4",
      "x": 22985.53183120697,
      "y": -455.898577055822,
      "width": 422.0745171302942,
      "height": 301.88674083086244,
      "z_value": -10.0,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "label": "Each Claude response node now picks a random emoji on creation (persisted in the data so it survives save/load), and paints it in the same top-left position as WarmNode's accent. Existing sessions without the field will get a fresh random pick on first load.",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": "#8a7a67"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "claude_response",
      "title": "Response",
      "uuid": "36ae72dce15d4797afb9653e87ea696f",
      "x": 23846.100060169738,
      "y": 792.1115848649106,
      "width": 420.0,
      "height": 204.0,
      "z_value": -10.0,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "label": "Good \u2014 `_run_vision` is only reachable via `_vision_rename` (eye button) and `_trigger_vision`. Let me check where `_trigger_vision` itself is called:",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": "#5a6a5a"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "about",
      "title": "TinkerBells Tantrum",
      "uuid": "c4b942a1931e44f39bf52df1522b71de",
      "x": 17487.46842488232,
      "y": 5533.820358688056,
      "width": 219.6362304488598,
      "height": 28.178176649919465,
      "z_value": -10.0,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": false,
      "label": "TinkerBells Tantrum",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": "#5a6a5a"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "claude_response",
      "title": "Response",
      "uuid": "3779881bad24459f8bdca8a7f2c9c5bb",
      "x": 16161.518300021338,
      "y": 2762.6762759032817,
      "width": 420.0,
      "height": 344.0,
      "z_value": -10.0,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "label": "Two issues: the `setup_iconic_button` uses `iconPadding` to shrink the icon inside the button, and `PrettyButton` uses `Theme.iconSize` (42px) while the .ico files max out at 256px layer. The padding is eating space, and the sidebar category buttons go through `setup_iconic_button` which subtracts padding.",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": "#9a4a4a"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "claude_response",
      "title": "Response",
      "uuid": "2729d91e1273422c890b4a62d10f2997",
      "x": 16819.824174148787,
      "y": 6078.176697087551,
      "width": 338.35189518173934,
      "height": 94.00578855980393,
      "z_value": -9.841000000000088,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "label": "The defensive View safety net",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "claude_response",
      "title": "Response",
      "uuid": "95091975813c4d5faa7fed2cb48f875f",
      "x": 15170.476851660453,
      "y": -21.679417846164142,
      "width": 420.0,
      "height": 232.0,
      "z_value": -9.745000000000141,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "label": "All 23 icons rebuilt with layers up to 256px, and `iconSize` now matches `iconButtonSize` at 48px \u2014 icons fill edge to edge with no padding shrinkage. PlayStation-dominant.",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "sequence",
      "title": "New folder",
      "uuid": "07fbcca4360e4c1787ff013cc07b6a55",
      "x": 14719.69064710454,
      "y": 4289.375914243612,
      "width": 320.0,
      "height": 300.0,
      "z_value": -9.726000000000152,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "folder_path": "C:\\Users\\thisg\\Desktop\\The Dawn of a new Era of Mankind\\Original Page Text\\03\\New folder",
      "current_frame": 4
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "claude_response",
      "title": "Response",
      "uuid": "914ecddea6964223b9b9a7aa556b477e",
      "x": 17771.457426087713,
      "y": 923.8818973399202,
      "width": 420.0,
      "height": 344.0,
      "z_value": -9.889000000000062,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "label": "The root cause fix: `to_dict()` no longer calls `_encode_to_b64()` for file-backed images \u2014 the data layer was already discarding the b64 for those, so the encode was pure wasted QPainter work. The suppression list catches any residual cases (e.g. paste-only images serialized before the render context is fully warm).",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "image",
      "title": "Image",
